# Project Specification: URL Shortener API

## Overview
Build a simple URL shortener REST API in Go.

## Requirements

### Core Features
- `POST /shorten` — Accepts a JSON body `{"url": "https://example.com"}` and returns a short code
- `GET /:code` — Redirects to the original URL
- `GET /stats/:code` — Returns visit count and creation date for a short URL

### Technical Details
- Language: Go (latest stable)
- Storage: SQLite (no external database required)
- Port: 8080 (configurable via `PORT` env var)
- Short codes: 6-character alphanumeric, randomly generated

### Testing
- Unit tests for the shortening logic
- Integration tests for the HTTP handlers
- Test with `go test ./...`

### Project Structure
```
cmd/server/main.go     — Entry point
internal/
  handler/             — HTTP handlers
  store/               — Database layer
  shortener/           — URL shortening logic
```
